  "prompt": "Why did Ian Mckellen have emotional breakdowns when on set on the Hobbit?",
  "response": "Ian McKellen experienced emotional difficulties while filming \"The Hobbit\" due to a combination of factors, including the extensive use of CGI (computer-generated imagery), the challenges of working with a much younger cast, and the pressures of the massive production. McKellen, who is renowned for his stage and film work, found the green screen environment and the reliance on digital effects to be particularly isolating and challenging, in contrast to the more traditional filmmaking methods he was used to.\n\nAdditionally, he faced the personal challenges of aging and the emotional weight of reprising a beloved character like Gandalf, which may have contributed to his feelings while on set. In interviews, McKellen described these moments as feeling disconnected and struggling with the nature of modern filmmaking, which sometimes made the experience less fulfilling for him. Nonetheless, he remained committed to his role and delivered a memorable performance despite these difficulties.",
